        ],
        [
          "A bookish priest who sees a true faith, in that vision he gets pulled in to vampire society. Trained by elder Tzi's for his lore, he moves on to find a pack of like minded people.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "staff"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were in eastern orthodox monk spent much time learning the politics of the church. After a period of time you realize that the politics was one thing but the signs of God was something much deeper. You had an ecstatic moment where you were able to see the truth of all the aspects of the trinity.  You attempted to tell your other brothers of this miracle that you had experienced but they attempted to calm you, a feeling that it was merely a bout of delusion. The message must have gone to someone who truly believed you. In that night you were kidnapped by revenants and taken to the manse of an elder Tzimise that lived in the times of Constantinople. He trained you in all the ways of lore that you currently hold dear. When it came time for your mortal form to weaken,  he had one of his younger children in brace you into the family.   Having his blessings you decided to follow your faith and go to the holy land there you fought members of other sects and eventually found true brotherhood in the vauldrie. You decided to follow the information that you had learned and go to Mexico City to see the priests of Caine. There you met La Petite Lunar and connected with them on a religious and personal level.  Your fellow brothers heard the call to Los Angeles and the prophets of your pack told you that this was where your destiny lay. In coming to Los Angeles you will fight demons both in the physical form in the heresy if your brothers."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Stanislav Kurpo",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "",
          "",
          "Clan",
          "Tzimisce - Bound to the Earth"
        ],
        [
